      "jurisdictional_notes": "Created 1883, organized 1905. NW ND. Named for Alexander McKenzie, political boss. Watford City is county seat. Bakken oil boom since 2006 — massive population growth. Theodore Roosevelt NP (North Unit). Fort Berthold Reservation partly in McKenzie.",
      "research_tips": "FamilySearch and McKenzie County Recorder (Watford City). Fort Union Trading Post National Historic Site — fur trade records at SHSND and NARA. Fort Buford (where Sitting Bull surrendered 1881) — military records at NARA. Missouri-Yellowstone confluence. Fort Berthold Reservation (MHA Nation) covers northern portion — tribal records at Fort Berthold Agency. Major Bakken oil boom county since 2008. Pre-1905 records under Billings County. SHSND microfilm.",
