      "research_tips": "FamilySearch and McLean County Recorder (Washburn). Fort Mandan site (Lewis & Clark winter 1804-1805). Fort Berthold Reservation (MHA Nation) in western portion — Garrison Dam (1953) inundated tribal communities and Old Sanish/Van Hook townsites. Garrison Dam relocation records at NARA. German-Russian and Scandinavian settlement in eastern portion. McLean County Historical Society in Washburn. SHSND microfilm.",
